<h1>March 16</h1>
<strong>Episode 5: The Showoff Gallery: A House Show Intensive:</strong>  This episode takes an in-depth look at The Showoff Gallery, one of the longest running all-ages spaces in Washington state. From 1990-2002, this warehouse on the wharfs of Bellingham Bay was a home to many artists who opened their doors to host shows, art events, proms, a 4 day all-woman circus, a 24-hour non-stop noise fest, and Showoff or Shutup Festival. (Clyde Petersen, Episode Producer)
