<strong>Episode 7: Thicker Than Blood:</strong>  Our Music, Ourselves and Our Community: This episode explores the social practices that surround the music. Highlights include the ruminations of a 30-something punk rocker who has always played an active role both as a touring musician and as a scene-maker in his community and who may well be concluding that the last ten years were a waste of time. Other segments share the stories of a Bellingham organization raising thousands of dollars for a new all-ages venue, bicycle-powered music shows, and fighting against city noise ordinances for the sake of art. (Matt Fuller; Episode Producer)
